  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Renforce the capacity of managers of sites of memory related to the slave trade and slavery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building inclusive and equitable development, based on ethical values and human rights, requires that institutions, communities and individuals, in particular women, are equipped with the capacities to confront their tragic history and manage the memory effectively. The Slave Route Project will support Member States and other stakeholders, to enhance their capacities to preserve, promote and manage the heritage of the slave trade and slavery by providing them guidelines and training to improve their pratices. To that end, a particular attention will be given to reinforcement of capacities of young women and men through their organizations and networks to play a leading role in the preservation and management of sites of memory.</narrative>
  </description>
